cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a design for WiFi networks to improve their lifetime, throughput, and fairness performance. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed design involves controlling the devices' sleep periods to improve their performance while satisfying their operation time requirement. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the near-far effect and hidden terminal problem in multiple AP scenarios, which are related to information theory. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The proposed design involves multiple devices working together to improve the performance of the network. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed design involves controlling the devices' behavior in a distributed manner to improve the performance of the network.
